name: Stendig Calendar
description:
I recently purchased one of these for the office, and after aimless staring at it, partly in admiration, I figured "why not try to make it in figma? y'know, as an exercise or whatever." So here we are. On top of all of that I also figured I'd share this contribution to the figma community.


I've size this based on a rough conversion from centimeters -> pixels, hence the weird decimals. I've also componentized and style-tokened all the pieces, so it can be changed fairly quickly, as any file should be.


Heck, make it your own, detach all the things.
